CommonFields.Title: Effect of inorganic phase on polymeric relaxation dynamics in PMMA/silica hybrids studied by dielectric analysis
Author: Li, Chaoxu
Wu, Juntao
Zhao, Jun
Zhao, Delu
Fan, Qingrong
CommonFields.Location: State Key Laboratory of Polymer Physics & Chemistry, Joint Laboratory of Polymer Science & Materials, Center for Molecular Science, Institute of Chemistry, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100080, PR China

Mixing.Description: PMMA was dissolved in THF at a concentration of 10 wt%.

Additive.Description: TEOS was added in various organic–inorganic ratios, 100/0, 80/20 and 60/40 (w/w) for PMMA/TEOS, and well mixed.
Then a 0.15M HCl aqueous solution was dropped in, always keeping a 4:1 molar water/TEOS stoichiometric proportion.

Mixing.Description: The solutions were further stirred for 16 h at ambient temperature.

MoldingInfo.Description: After stirring, the solutions were cast onto Teflon dishes.

Drying-Evaporation.Description: The drying process was carried out at 60°C for 12 h, then 110°C in vacuum for another 12 h.

ChooseParameter.Other: The final films with the thickness of ca. 0.3–0.4 mm were stored in a desiccator before other measurements.

Transmission_Electron_Microscopy.EquipmentUsed: Their morphologies were observed by transmission electron microscopy (TEM).

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: Dynamic mechanical spectra were recorded on a Rheometric Scientific DMTA V apparatus using the rectangular tension mode.

Dielectric_and_Impedance_Spectroscopy_An.Description: Dielectric measurements were performed using the dielectric analyzer, DEA 2970 (TA Instruments). The samples were sandwiched between the ceramic parallel plate sensors (the diameter was 25 mm), and exerted by a maximum force of ca. 300 N to ensure good contact between the samples and the electrodes.

Differential_Scanning_Calorimetry.Description: Samples of ca. 4.0 mg were sealed in aluminum pans, and their thermal properties were measured by using a TA2910 DSC. Indium and tin were employed for the temperature calibration, and all scans were performed under an ultra-high-purity nitrogen gas purge with a flux of ca. 30 ml/min.

Fourier_Transform_Infrared_Spectroscopy.Description: Films with a thickness suitable for FTIR measurements were prepared by compressing the samples at 180°C directly.

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: The contents of SiO2 were determined by thermal gravimetric analysis (TGA) at the heating rate of 20°C/min to 800°C.

SampleSize.description: DMA sample size: 5 mm x 25 mm
